      "level": 2,
      "text": "Design has a material footprint that the profession rarely discusses with precision. The fonts we serve, the images we compress (or fail to), the animations we run, the hardware refresh cycles our software demands — each carries an energy cost. This paper maps the environmental impact of design practice and proposes principles for a more careful discipline.",
